  <static seed="269" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionAdditionWordProblems10.pg">
    <statement><p>Corey walked <m>{{\frac{3}{11}}}</m> of a mile in the morning, and then walked <m>{{\frac{1}{12}}}</m> of a mile in the afternoon. How far did Corey walk altogether?</p>
<p>Corey walked a total of <fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/> of a mile.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{47}{132}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>This is an addition problem.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{3}{11}}} + {{\frac{1}{12}}} 
      \amp = \frac{3 \cdot 12}{11 \cdot 12}+\frac{1 \cdot 11}{12 \cdot 11} \\
      \amp = \frac{36}{132} + \frac{11}{132} \\
      \amp = \frac{36+11}{132} \\
      
      \amp = {{\frac{47}{132}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Corey walked a total of <m>{{\frac{47}{132}}}</m> miles altogether.</p>
</solution>
